<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Test_for_differences_in_ozo=
ne_levels_by_month">Test for differences in ozone levels by month</h3><span=
 class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DKruskal%E2%80%93Walli=
s_test&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Test for d=
ifferences in ozone levels by month"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw=
-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The following example uses data from Chambers et al.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kruskal%E2=
%80%93Wallis_test#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
on daily readings of ozone for May 1 to September 30, 1973, in New York Cit=
y. The data are in the R data set <code>airquality</code>, and the analysis=
 is included in the documentation for the R function <code>kruskal.test</co=
de>. Boxplots of ozone values by month are shown in the figure.
</p><p><span typeof=3D"mw:File"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fi=
le:Ozone_by_month_boxplots.svg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"h=
ttps://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Ozone_by_month_box=
plots.svg/330px-Ozone_by_month_boxplots.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"300" height=3D"216" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"366" d=
ata-file-height=3D"264"></a></span>
</p><p>The Kruskal=E2=80=93Wallis test finds a significant difference (p =
=3D 6.901e-06) indicating that ozone differs among the 5 months.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-r mw-content-ltr" dir=3D"ltr">=
<pre><span></span><span class=3D"nf">kruskal.test</span><span class=3D"p">(=
</span><span class=3D"n">Ozone</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"o">~</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">Month</span><spa=
n class=3D"p">,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">data</spa=
n><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> =
</span><span class=3D"n">airquality</span><span class=3D"p">)</span>

<span class=3D"w">	</span><span class=3D"n">Kruskal</span><span class=3D"o"=
>-</span><span class=3D"n">Wallis</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span cla=
ss=3D"n">rank</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">sum</span><=
span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">test</span>

<span class=3D"n">data</span><span class=3D"o">:</span><span class=3D"w">  =
</span><span class=3D"n">Ozone</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"n">by</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">Month</span>
<span class=3D"n">Kruskal</span><span class=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"n"=
>Wallis</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">chi</span><span c=
lass=3D"o">-</span><span class=3D"n">squared</span><span class=3D"w"> </spa=
n><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"m">2=
9.267</span><span class=3D"p">,</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"n">df</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span=
 class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"m">4</span><span class=3D"p">,</span><s=
pan class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">p</span><span class=3D"o">-</span=
><span class=3D"n">value</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=
=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"m">6.901e-06</span>
</pre></div>
<p>To determine which months differ, post-hoc tests may be performed using =
a Wilcoxon test for each pair of months, with a Bonferroni (or other) corre=
